@page "/"

<PageTitle>Llama.Grammar - GBNF Converter</PageTitle>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Llama.Grammar</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                Convert JSON Schemas, C# types, and regular expressions to GBNF (Grammar-Based Next-Token Format) grammars for AI models.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">JSON Schema to GBNF</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Convert JSON Schema definitions to GBNF grammars using our fluent builder API or raw JSON.
                    </p>
                    <a href="json-schema" class="btn btn-primary">Try JSON Schema</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">C# Type to GBNF</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Generate GBNF grammars directly from C# class definitions, including nested objects and collections.
                    </p>
                    <a href="csharp-type" class="btn btn-primary">Try C# Types</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Regex to GBNF</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Convert regular expressions to GBNF format for pattern-based text generation.
                    </p>
                    <a href="regex" class="btn btn-primary">Try Regex</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h2>About GBNF</h2>
            <p>
                GBNF (Grammar-Based Next-Token Format) is used by AI models like LLaMA, Mistral, and GPT to constrain 
                their outputs to specific formats and structures. This ensures that the generated text follows your 
                desired schema, making it perfect for structured data generation, API responses, and more.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="mt-4">Features</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                <li>🧱 Fluent builder API for creating JSON Schema objects in C#</li>
                <li>🧠 Converts JSON Schema to GBNF</li>
                <li>✅ Supports complex schema features like:
                    <ul class="mt-2">
                        <li>Nested objects</li>
                        <li>Arrays and array constraints</li>
                        <li>Enums and constants</li>
                        <li>Required fields</li>
                        <li>Pattern matching</li>
                        <li>Nullable types</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="mt-4">
                <a href="https://github.com/jihadkhawaja/Llama.Grammar" class="btn btn-outline-secondary me-2">
                    View on GitHub
                </a>
                <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/Llama.Grammar" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">
                    NuGet Package
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
